 anti-inflammatory activities, which may contribute to its potential health benefits. Studies have also indicated that Ficus triloba may have antioxidant properties, helping to protect the body against free radicals and oxidative stress. Additionally, the plant's extracts may exhibit cardiovascular-protective effects, potentially lowering blood pressure and cholesterol levels. More research is needed to confirm the full extent of Ficus triloba's health benefits.", "parts": "Ficus triloba is reported to have various medicinal properties, although more research is needed to confirm these uses. The leaves, bark, and roots of Ficus triloba are traditionally used in herbal medicine. Ficus triloba leaves are said to have anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties. The plant is also used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues. However, the effectiveness and safety of using Ficus triloba for medicinal purposes require further scientific investigation.", "intro": "The Ficus triloba, also known as the three-lobed fig, is a plant species belonging to the family Moraceae, native to tropical Asia. Traditionally, the leaves and stems of Ficus triloba have been used in herbal medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions, due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The plant's bioactive constituents include flavonoids, alkaloids, and glycosides, which have been shown to possess antioxidant, anti-cancer, and anti-inflammatory activities. In traditional herbal medicine, Ficus triloba is often prepared as a decoction, infusion, or tincture, and is used to treat a range of conditions, including digestive issues, respiratory problems, and menstrual disorders."}